# Privacy Policy for lumira

**Effective Date:** 2025.03.18

lumira ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our mobile application.

---

## 1. Overview

lumira is an offline-first document reader designed to open and read files stored locally on your device.

We prioritize user privacy:
- No account required
- No mandatory data upload
- Most features work fully offline

---

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 Personal Data

We do not directly collect personally identifiable information such as your name, email address, or phone number.

---

### 2.2 Device & Usage Data

We may collect limited non-personal data for app improvement, including:

- Device model and operating system
- App usage interactions
- Crash reports and diagnostics

---

### 2.3 Files and Documents

The app allows you to access and read files stored on your device.

- We do NOT collect, upload, or store your files on our servers
- All document access is performed locally on your device

---

## 3. Advertising

We use third-party advertising services to display ads in the app.

These services may collect certain information automatically, including:

- Advertising ID (e.g. Google Advertising ID)
- Device information
- Interaction data (e.g. ad impressions, clicks)

This data may be used to provide personalized or non-personalized ads.

### Advertising partners include:

- Google AdMob  
  https://policies.google.com/privacy

- AppLovin  
  https://www.applovin.com/privacy/

We do not control how these third-party services collect or use your data. Please review their privacy policies for more details.

---

## 4. AI Features

If you use AI-powered features (such as text summarization or explanation):

- Selected text may be sent to third-party AI service providers
- Data is processed only to provide the requested feature
- We do NOT use your data for training AI models
- AI processing is triggered only by user action

---

## 5. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data.

We may share limited information with:

- Advertising partners (for ad delivery)
- Analytics or crash reporting tools (if applicable)

All third-party services are required to handle data in accordance with their privacy policies.

---

## 6. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information.

However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.

---

## 7. Your Privacy Rights

Depending on your location (e.g. EEA, UK, California), you may have rights including:

- Request access to your data  
- Request deletion of your data  
- Opt out of personalized advertising  

You can also:

- Reset or limit your Advertising ID in device settings  
- Disable personalized ads through your system settings  

---

## 8. Children's Privacy

This app is not intended for children under the age of 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

---

## 9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.

